tmjos (2.0.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Rebase em Debian 13 (trixie). Sai do ciclo Ubuntu.
  * Remove Depends em tmjos-dock, tmjos-shell-tweaks, tmjos-installer
    (Ubuntu-only — substituídos por Calamares + GNOME nativo em v2.0).
  * Add zram-tools + preload em Recommends (target idle ~2GB RAM).
  * Add evolution em Recommends (Exchange compat).
  * Add calamares + calamares-settings-debian em Recommends (installer).
  * Atualiza description pra Debian-based.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Tue, 12 May 2026 21:30:00 -0300

tmjos (1.3.4-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add tmjmenu (>= 1.3.4) to Depends — proprietary application
    menu + dock that replaces the GNOME Activities Overview and the
    Plank dock. tmjmenu postinst disables Plank autostart automatically.
  * tmjos-dock package remains in Depends because its other scripts
    (tmjos-first-run, tmjos-dock-sync, tmjos-show-apps) provide
    backward-compat behavior used by some users / fallback.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Mon, 11 May 2026 16:40:00 -0300

tmjos (1.3.0-2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add tmjos-installer (>= 1.3.0) to Depends — fixes "ISO ships
    without an installer" issue in v1.3.0-1 (snapd was removed by
    slim phase, taking Ubuntu 24.04's default installer with it).
  * Bump tmjpad requirement to >= 0.1.2 (icon-not-appearing fix
    via /usr/share/pixmaps/ fallback).

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Sun, 10 May 2026 22:10:00 -0300

tmjos (1.3.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial metapackage release.
  * Depends on the five tmjos-* core packages + tmjpad.
  * Recommends mirror the v1.2 ISO's preinstalled set (VSCode, Docker,
    Git, fonts, network tools, etc).
  * `sudo apt install tmjos` on a base Ubuntu 24.04 turns it into
    TMJOs. `sudo apt upgrade tmjos` pulls latest versions of every
    component — the v1.3 update mechanism in one command.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Sun, 10 May 2026 19:45:00 -0300
